content:
Addressed all comments.
@abarth interesting ideas for how to improve the performance. I'd like to investigate the first option once the initial CL lands. Having a custom PipelineOwner could be interesting for other reasons as wel.
Keep in mind the current design at feels like it has fine performance for the applications I've tested with likely because the UI I need to render in the overlay is extremely simple. Note that the TextPainter is now cached almost all times when the selected RenderObject does not change. The current UI is as complex as the UI rendered within the screen area for Chrome Devtools so I expect there is a good change we do not need to render anything more sophisticated on the device screen to provide a good developer experience.

@stuartmorgan 

> And a design document is the best place to have a discussion like that.

I get it. I will create a document, so please give me some more time.
